Reference - Authors: B E Gewurz; R Gaudet; D Tortorella; E W Wang; H L Ploegh; D C Wiley
Reference - Journal: Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A
Reference - Title: Antigen presentation subverted: Structure of the human cytomegalovirus protein US2 bound to the class I molecule HLA-A2.
Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Assay - Comments: The crystal structure contains the MHC/epitope complex bound to the human cytomegalovirus (HCMV) glycoprotein US2 (Unique Short). The crystallographic asymmetric unit contains four copies the US2/MHC/Peptide complex. The following residues had a well ordered electron density and were included in the refined atomic model: MHC: 1-275, β2-microglobulin 0-99, Tax epitope: 1-9, US2:43-137. No electron density was observed for US2 residues 15–42 and 138–140. The US2 binding site on the MHC molecule is distant from the epitope binding groove and does not affect the MHC/peptide binding.

Reference - Authors: S Demaria; L D DeVito-Haynes; R D Salter; W J Burlingham; Y Bushkin
Reference - Title: Peptide-conformed beta2m-free class I heavy chains are intermediates in generation of soluble HLA by the membrane-bound metalloproteinase.
Epitope - Source Organism: Human T-cell leukemia virus type I
Epitope - Comments: Sequence of epitope can be found in reference Parker et al. [PMID: 1517560].
Assay - Comments: A HLA-A*0201 mutant (HLA-A2.242K) that has a Gln-242 substituted for Lys in the heavy chain (HC) and a reduced affinity to beta-2-microglobulin (b-2-m) was tested.  It was shown that conformations of HLA-A2.242K HC are stabilized by peptide-binding without b-2-m.  Cell-bound and b-2-m-free HLA molecules that are enzyme MPase-cleaved and released into solution were able to retain conformation and reassociate with exogenous b-2-m.  The b-2-m was effective in protecting cell-bound HC from MPase proteolysis.

Reference - Title: Chicken major histocompatibility complex class II molecules of the B haplotype present self and foreign peptides.
Epitope - Source Organism: Reticuloendotheliosis virus
Antigen Processing - Comments: To obtain a source of B-L molecules, cells of bursa of Fabricius of 15.N-21 and 15.P-19 chickens, possessing B21 and B19 MHC haplotypes, respectively, were transformed with reticuloendotheliosis virus (REV)-T strain. Antigen Processing - Comments: To obtain a source of B-L molecules, cells of bursa of Fabricius of 15.N-21 and 15.P-19 chickens, possessing B21 and B19 MHC haplotypes, respectively, were transformed with reticuloendotheliosis virus (REV)-T strain. For immunoaffinity purification of surface B-L molecules, approximately 1.5X1010 cells from each of the B19 and B21 transformed B cell lines were harvested, lysed and filtered.

Reference - Authors: G G Burrows; K Ariail; B Celnik; J E Gambee; H Offner; A A Vandenbark
Reference - Title: Multiple class I motifs revealed by sequencing naturally processed peptides eluted from rat T cell MHC molecules.
Epitope - Source Organism: AKR (endogenous) murine leukemia virus
Antigen Processing - Comments: The Vb8.21 T cell hybridoma C14/BW12-12A1 (A1 hybridoma) was created by fusing an encephalitogenic LEW(RT11) T cell clone specific for Gp-BP-72-89 with a TCR (a/b) negative thymoma, BW5147. The A1 hybridoma expressed rat MHC class I, rat TCR Vb8.2 and rat CD4. Class I molecules were purified by immuno-affinity chromatography from detergent extracts and bound peptides were dissociated from MHC by acid treatment, separated by HPLC and sequenced following Edman degradation.
Assay - Comments: Anchor residues were shown to be L at P3 and S at P9. Preferred residues were Y, V, K, F, I, L or H at P1, D, E, Q, G or R at P2, P at P4, N or K at P5, W or K at P6, T at P7 and Y, M or E at P8.

Reference - Title: Natural ligand motifs of H-2E molecules are allele specific and illustrate homology to HLA-DR molecules.
Epitope - Source Molecule: env polyprotein - murine endogenous virus EMV-1 (fragment)
Epitope - Source Organism: Murine endogenous retrovirus
Antigen Processing - Comments: H-2-Ed molecules were purified from A20 or LQ-9E10 cells using allele-specific 14-4-4S antibodies. Bound MHC molecules were treated with TFA to elute associated peptides and the peptide containing supernatants were separated by reversed-phase HPLC. Peptides eluting in large distinct peaks were sequenced individually by Edman degradation.
Assay - Comments: Natural ligand motifs of H-2E molecules are allele specific and illustrate homology to HLA-DR molecules.
